                        if triangle_aabb_intersection(&vertices, &child.lock().unwrap().aabb) {
                            child.lock().unwrap().insert(&mut leaves.clone(), face_index, vertices, max_depth, depth + 1);
                        }
                    }
                )
            }
        }
    }
}


```

The error you're encountering occurs due to the temporary value created by `leaves.clone()` being dropped while you still have a borrow on it. The root of the issue here is using the `.clone()` method, which creates a new `Arc` that does not have the same lifetime constraints as the original `leaves`.

To resolve this, we can modify the code to avoid borrowing from a temporary object. Instead, we should directly pass the original `leaves` reference.

Here is the fixed code, focusing on the `insert` method and how `leaves` is passed around:

