The problem you're encountering is that you are trying to mutably borrow `root` multiple times within a loop, leading to a borrow checker error. This happens because Rust does not allow multiple mutable references to the same data at the same time to ensure memory safety.

To fix this problem, we can refactor the code such that we do not need to hold multiple mutable references to `root`. One way to achieve this is by changing the borrow model to avoid conflicts and potentially using a design pattern that ensures exclusive access is always maintained properly.

